   <section id="donors">
    <h2>
     Recognizing Our Donors
    </h2>
    <article class="intro">
     <p>
      <strong>
       If CSUF students and faculty are the heart of our University, then donors are the backbone.
      </strong>
     </p>
     <p>
      The ways to make a difference are as diverse as our donors: scholarships; endowed chairs and professorships; special programs and centers; the building and renovation of facilities. We salute the many donors since our founding who have helped CSUF become the exceptional institution it is today, and invite you to join their distinguished ranks.
     </p>
     <br/>
     <p align="center">
      <a class="pill" href="http://news.fullerton.edu/_resources/pdfs/CSUF-2018-Annual-Report.pdf">
       2018 Honor Roll
      </a>
      <a class="pill" href="ontiveros-society/">
       Ontiveros Legacy Society
      </a>
     </p>
    </article>
    <article>
     <ul>
      <li>
       <a href="features/humanities-scholars.aspx">
        <img alt="Vivian Ngo, Daniella Camacho, Danielle Narcisco, and Ileana Perez" src="_resources/images/donors/2018/scholars.jpg"/>
        <h3>
         Empowering the Next Generation of Humanities Scholars
        </h3>
       </a>
       <p>
        The new
        <span class="highlight">
         Mellon Mays Undergraduate Fellowship
        </span>
        increases academic opportunities and provide financial support for students planning to pursue doctoral degrees in the humanities immediately after completing their bachelor’s degrees.
       </p>
      </li>
      <li>
       <a href="features/sport-performance.aspx">
        <img alt="Student athlete is being monitored while running on treadmill." src="_resources/images/donors/2018/sport-performance.jpg"/>
        <h3>
         Exploring the Science of Athletics
        </h3>
       </a>
       <p>
        At the
        <span class="highlight">
         Center for Sport Performance
        </span>
        , kinesiology faculty and student researchers are applying scientific innovation and technology to study every aspect of the body’s training process — from cellular changes to biomechanics — and help athletes achieve peak performance.
       </p>
      </li>
      <li>
       <a href="features/family-business.aspx">
        <img alt=" Cindy Ayloush" src="_resources/images/donors/2018/family.jpg"/>
        <h3>
         A Boost for Family Businesses
        </h3>
       </a>
       <p>
        <span class="highlight">
         The Center for Family Business
        </span>
        help family businesses succeed and maintain their legacy.
       </p>
      </li>
      <li>
       <a href="features/oral-history.aspx">
        <img alt="Students examining soldier uniform." src="_resources/images/donors/2018/oral.jpg"/>
        <h3>
         Where Oral History and Scholarship Meet
        </h3>
       </a>
       <p>
        <span class="highlight">
         The Lawrence de Graaf Center for Oral and Public History
        </span>
        preserves history by providing a way for students and researchers to access vital information about the past and present — and to make connections to the future.
       </p>
      </li>
      <!--<li><a href="features/safe.aspx"><img src="_resources/images/donors/2017/safe.jpg" alt="Project SAFE"/>
                          <h3>Creating a Safety Net for Students</h3></a><p>While students may face obstacles on their path to a college
degree, lacking food or shelter shouldn't be one of them. It is this
belief that spurred Division of Student Affairs
							to launch a <span class="highlight">Food and Housing Security Task Force</span> to address the
issues on campus.</p></li>
                        <li><a href="features/women-leadership.aspx"><img src="_resources/images/donors/2017/women-leaders.jpg" alt="Women Leadership"/>
                          <h3>Developing Women Leadership</h3></a><p>Cal State Fullerton was one of four campuses in the nation
							chosen to participate in the <span class="highlight">BOLD Women's Leadership Network</span>,
which supports female cohorts at the junior class level through
scholarships and mentoring to help them develop leadership
skills and transform themselves and their communities.</p></li>-->
     </ul>
    </article>
